elements.description:
`<vaadin-radio-button>` is a Polymer element for radio buttons.

```html
<vaadin-radio-button value="foo">Foo</vaadin-radio-button>
```

### Styling

The following shadow DOM parts are available for styling:

Part name         | Description
------------------|----------------
`radio`           | The radio button element
`label`           | The label content element

The following state attributes are available for styling:

Attribute  | Description | Part name
-----------|-------------|------------
`disabled`   | Set when the radio button is disabled. | :host
`focus-ring` | Set when the radio button is focused using the keyboard. | :host
`focused`    | Set when the radio button is focused. | :host
`checked`    | Set when the radio button is checked. | :host

See [ThemableMixin – how to apply styles for shadow parts](https://github.com/vaadin/vaadin-themable-mixin/wiki)

properties.name: autofocus
properties.description: Specify that this control should have input focus when the page loads.

properties.name: _previousTabIndex
properties.description: Stores the previous value of tabindex attribute of the disabled element

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: If true, the user cannot interact with this element.

properties.name: checked
properties.description: True if the radio button is checked.

methods.name: focus
methods.description: Moving the focus from the host element causes firing of the blur event what leads to problems in IE.

methods.name: blur
methods.description:
Native bluring in the host element does nothing because it does not have the focus.
In chrome it works, but not in FF.

methods.name: _addEventListenerToNode
methods.description: Add the event listener to the node if it is a gestures event.

params.name: node
params.description: Node to add event listener to

methods.name: _removeEventListenerFromNode
methods.description: Remove the event listener to the node if it is a gestures event.

params.name: node
params.description: Node to remove event listener from

elements.description:
`<vaadin-radio-group>` is a Polymer element for grouping vaadin-radio-buttons.

```html
<vaadin-radio-group>
  <vaadin-radio-button name="foo">Foo</vaadin-radio-button>
  <vaadin-radio-button name="bar">Bar</vaadin-radio-button>
  <vaadin-radio-button name="baz">Baz</vaadin-radio-button>
</vaadin-radio-group>
```

### Styling

The following shadow DOM parts are available for styling:

Part name | Description
----------------|----------------
`label` | The label element

The following state attributes are available for styling:

Attribute  | Description | Part name
-----------|-------------|------------
`disabled` | Set when the radio group and its children are disabled. | :host
`has-label` | Set when the element has a label | :host

See [ThemableMixin – how to apply styles for shadow parts](https://github.com/vaadin/vaadin-themable-mixin/wiki)

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: The current disabled state of the radio group. True if group and all internal radio buttons are disabled.

properties.name: label
properties.description: String used for the label element.

elements.name: Vaadin.RadioGroupElement

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: The current disabled state of the radio group. True if group and all internal radio buttons are disabled.

attributes.name: label
attributes.description: String used for the label element.
